H0.text: Stomach, esophagus, large intestine, small intestine is the correct order of food traveling through the digestive system after it is swallowed.

H1.text: Small intestine, large intestine, esophagus, stomach is the correct order of food traveling through the digestive system after it is swallowed.

H2.text: Esophagus, stomach, large intestine, small intestine is the correct order of food traveling through the digestive system after it is swallowed.

H3.text: Esophagus, stomach, small intestine, large intestine is the correct order of food traveling through the digestive system after it is swallowed.

A4.text: The esophagus is thus one of the first components of the digestive system and the gastrointestinal tract.

A5.text: After food passes through the esophagus, it enters the stomach.
